---
import { site, education, certifications } from '../data/site';
---

<section id="about" class="section">
  <div class="container-x">
    <div class="grid gap-16 md:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr]">
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="heading-eyebrow">About</span>
        <h2 class="h-display mt-4 text-4xl md:text-5xl">
          Engineer who likes the boring,<br />load-bearing parts.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 120ms;">
        <div class="space-y-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-text/75 md:text-lg">
          <p>
            I'm a backend Java engineer based in the {site.location}. I'm happiest
            when I'm tightening a hot path with JFR, replacing an N+1 with a
            proper fetch join, or wiring a Spring Boot service to a Kafka topic
            that downstream consumers can actually rely on.
          </p>
          <p>
            Lately I've been deep in <span class="text-accent"
              >Retrieval Augmented Generation</span
            > with Spring AI and LangChain4j, and benchmarking
            <span class="text-accent2">Java Virtual Threads</span> against the older
            executor world. I publish the benchmarks and write up the tradeoffs
            on GitHub so the work isn't just a claim on a resume.
          </p>
          <p>
            I own services end-to-end: API contract, schema, deploy,
            observability, and the on-call pager. I'd rather ship one durable
            service than five clever ones.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-10 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="card p-5">
            <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-muted">
              Education
            </div>
            <div class="mt-2 font-display text-base font-semibold">
              {education.school}
            </div>
            <div class="mt-1 text-sm text-text/70">{education.degree}</div>
            <div class="mt-1 text-xs text-muted">
              GPA {education.gpa} · Graduated {education.graduated}
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card p-5">
            <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-muted">
              Certifications
            </div>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-2">
              {
                certifications.map((c) => (
                  <li class="text-sm">
                    <div class="font-medium text-text">{c.name}</div>
                    <div class="text-xs text-muted">
                      {c.date}
                      {c.score ? ` · Score ${c.score}` : ''}
                    </div>
                  </li>
                ))
              }
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
